"sentence\": \"Their friendly rivalry has driven both to greater heights.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their friendly rivalry\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"greater heights\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They each won two golds and four medals at these games, which pushed Ledecky to 14 overall and left the 23-year-old Aussie with four golds and eight medals in her career.\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two golds\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2278}, {\"ngram\": \"four medals\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"these games\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2309}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"the 23-year-old Aussie\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"four golds\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"eight medals\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To think that \\u2026 I challenged her into her fourth consecutive in the 800 is pretty cool,\\\" Titmus said.\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2517, \"end\": 2523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel very honored and privileged to be her rival, and I hope I have made her a better athlete.\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her rival\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has certainly made me become the athlete I am.\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2672}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt so privileged to race alongside her.\\\"\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has dominated the distance freestyle events over the last dozen years - and is not done yet.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2732}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance freestyle events\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"the last dozen years\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's made it clear she plans to keep swimming at least through the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Games\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not easy,\\\" Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 2949, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will take it year by year, and we will see if I can keep giving everything I have got for as long as I have left in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 3073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Summer McIntoshstamped herself as one of the swimming stars of the Paris Olympics with her third individual gold medal, winning the 200 individual medley.\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Summer McIntoshstamped\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3097}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming stars\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3134}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 3138, \"to\": 3156}, {\"ngram\": \"her third individual gold medal\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200 individual medley\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old Canadian chased down American Alex Walsh and held off another U.S. swimmer, Kate Douglass, to finish in an Olympic record of 2:06.56.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3247, \"end\": 3255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999895271514997, \"rank\": 1.0472951719232906e-05, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3268, \"end\": 3276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999766365700351, \"rank\": 2.2806736345095204e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3277, \"end\": 3287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 3323, \"end\": 3336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another U.S. swimmer\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3321}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic record\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"2:06.56\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Douglass grabbed the silver in the star-studded final at 2:06.92, but the Americans lost the bronze when Walsh, the silver medalist in this event at Tokyo who recorded a time of 2:07.06, was disqualified because she did not finish the backstroke segment on her back.\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3382, \"end\":